      "id": "spine_biology_l4_cardiac_ap_ventricular",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_action_potential",
      "content": {
        "title": "Cardiac Action Potential Overview (Non-Pacemaker)",
        "definition": "A comparative overview of ventricular myocyte action potentials highlighting prolonged depolarization from calcium influx creating a plateau phase, distinct from brief neuronal action potentials.",
        "summary": "Cardiac myocytes have a longer action potential due to L-type calcium channel-mediated plateau. Detailed phase 0–4 ionic currents belong under cardiac membrane potential L3; this node establishes contrast only."
      },
